ason, just to know how we are doing!\n\n- honeya\n|\nJoy, joy, joy!Past ages crowd on thee, but each one remembers,And the future is dark, and the present is spread,Like a pillow of thorns for thy slumberless head.\n\n- Percy Bysshe Shelley, Prometheus Unbound\n|\nOur capacity can grow or diminish, and either way, the results compound over time.\n\n- Audrey\n|\nThe wages of sin are death, but by the time taxes are taken out, it's just sort of a tired feeling.\n\n- Paula\n|\nI mean, maybe I am crazy. I mean, maybe. But if this is all there is, then I don't want to be sane.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, Neverwhere\n|\nPardon me if, reading that, I want to laugh, because you want to relieve me of a fear I've never had. I've never thought that, as they say, you eat little children.\n\n- Jeanne\n|\nThe thing that had been, it is that which shall be; And that which is done is that which shall be done.\n\n- Compton\n|\nI love you,' he murmurs. 'Can you feel that? You. Not some destiny I think I'm called to. You. I'm with you. My strength. My soul. My heart. Feel it.\n\n- Cynthia Hand, Boundless\n|\nSurviving is good, but overcoming is better.\n\n- Shelley\n|\nMuch of your strength as a woman can come from the resolve to replenish and fill your own well and essence first, before taking care of others.\n\n- Miranda J. Barrett, A Woman's Truth: A Life Truly Worth Living\n|\nI wanted to see her sad. Taste her tears. I wanted to know what she sounded like when she cried. In pain, in pleasure, in both.\n\n- T.M. Frazier, Preppy: The Life & Death of Samuel Clearwater, Part One\n|\nAnd at twelve, heading for adulthood, a child fears that the way she is at that moment is all she's ever going to be.\n\n- Jane\n|\nFear is what keeps the walls up, so open the gate and let what you want, in when you want\n\n- Joshua\n|\nThe more the Word of God abides in a person, the more strength and wisdom he will have.\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIf you keep the burden on your head, God (Bhagwan) will move away.\n\n- Dada