r.\n\n- Albert\n|\nHere today, may be gone tomorrow! Never take anyone or nothing for granted! Be sure to count your blessing daily because tomorrow isn't promised.\n\n- Surgeo\n|\nBeauty fades, but knowledge is eternal\n\n- Andrew\n|\nThankfully, the nature of pain reminds us of what the ease of pleasure foolishly allows us to forget.\n\n- Craig\n|\nI'm in love with you.''Good grief.' She kept walking.\n\n- Tahereh\n|\nWhen a person is loved, they are granted the strength of all seas.\n\n- Simon Van Booy, The Secret Lives of People in Love\n|\nI think getting married was a mistake along the way, but at the same time I wouldn't have the wonderful children I have if I didn't get married.\n\n- Hugh\n|\nI tried to look at writing a song almost like solving a mystery. The song was there, buried somewhere in my brain. All I had to do was follow the clues until I figured it out.\n\n- Jon Skovron, Struts & Frets\n|\nWith grace, we find the strength within to reach the goal.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nUnhappy people do the oddest, most terrible things, just trying to keep despair at bay. All you have to do is accept them...go around them...take evasive action.\n\n- Geraldine\n|\nI don't run away from a challenge because I am afraid. Instead, I run towards it because the only way to escape fear is to trample it beneath your foot\n\n- Nadia\n|\nFor despite what some people say, love is not only a sweet falling bound to come and quickly go away.\n\n- Erich\n|\nThe word try, means nothing. There's no such thing as trying to do something. The moment you begin a task, you're doing it. So just finish what you're doing.\n\n- La Tisha Honor, Teen Roach\n|\nI sleep with the lights on now. Not because I’m afraid of the dark, but because I like to keep the night as far away as I can.\n\n- Keith Kekic, Nightwalkers\n|\nI was so good at being a kid, and so terrible at being whatever I was now.\n\n- John Green, Turtles All the Way Down\n|\nThe way you treat people who are in no position to help you,