erstand what it is to be loved and forgiven, then loved even more.” Pastel Orphans\n\n- Gemma Liviero, Pastel Orphans\n|\nWhen I don’t take action in spite of doubt and fear, I lose 100%.\n\n- Dhaval Gajera, MAKE IT HAPPEN: with 30 greatest life lessons\n|\nImmortals are constrained by ancient rules. But a hero can go anywhere, challenge anyone, as long as he has the nerve.-Chiron\n\n- Rick\n|\nWhen in trouble, run to God. When in pain, dwell in His presence. When you don't know what to say or do, ask God and for every moment praise God. He is always by your side!\n\n- Gift\n|\nAll I know is this: nobody's very big in the first place, and it looks to me like everybody spends their whole life tearing everybody else down.\n\n- Ken Kesey, One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest\n|\nThe idea of being vulnerable leaves a lot of room for choice. There is always room to be less foldable, more evil.\n\n- Sherry Turkle, Alone Together: Why We Expect More from Technology and Less from Each Other\n|\nBecause of fear, people who have civil rights can’t use them\n\n- Sunday\n|\nI sought to hear the voice of God and climbed the topmost steeple, but God declared: 'Go down again - I dwell among the people.\n\n- John\n|\nDo what you can, when you can.\n\n- Johnny Worthen, The Brand Demand\n|\nWe are given a great power, we should capable enough to handle it and use it fair and square.\n\n- Rhealyn\n|\nThere is a bright to even the darkest circumstance, if you have the courage to look for it.\n\n- Unknown\n|\nChaos limits the free-flow of love and becomes a roadblock to what family members want most and sadly, it becomes the normal for the family.\n\n- David\n|\nThe wiser I become, the less I think beauty has anything to do with appearance.\n\n- Steve\n|\nTherapy is not to 'talk about' things, but to change the person's life, and to relieve suffering, such as depression, anxiety, or relationship problems.\n\n- David\n|\nIf you fall in love, you feel forever young.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWhat you call pride, I call courage.\n\n- Jeff Zentner, The Serpent King\n|\nI must loss everything, to gain anything that Christ Jesus has for me under the power of His grace.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nI like a girl with a substantial bottom,' said Renoir, drawing in the air the size bottom he preferred.\n\n- Christopher Moore, Sacré Bleu: A Comedy d'Art\n|\nWhen you aim for the stars even if you fail you’ll be a falling star, and that’s wish-fulfilling material.\n\n- Kevin\n|\nThere are so many challenges, but the first, closest and biggest challenge is our mindset!\n\n- Ernest\n|\nShe wanted to lose herself in him. To tie his arms around her like a tourniquet.If she showed him how much she needed him, he'd run away.\n\n- Rainbow Rowell, Eleanor & Park\n|\nIn the darkness time, the soul evolves to give light to the spirit.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nShe'd be dead before the memories and pain were finally gone; she knew it, accepted it, and dealt with it.\n\n- Catherine\n|\nI’ve always thought the best songs come though us not from us…. They gave me life, they gave me an identity and I gave them my tears, my heart, and my truth.\n\n- Carole Bayer Sager, They're Playing Our Song\n|\nI will listen to a beautiful person much more quickly than a plain person, and I have to learn to be nice to people who are not attractive looking.\n\n- Beatrice\n|\nI'd prefer to be alone by myself,than alone in a room full of people.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nHappiness cannot be traveled to, owned, earned, worn or consumed. Happiness is a spiritual experience of living every moment with love, grace and gratitude.\n\n- Dennis\n|\nI’m not going to be part of this,” said Leo. He opened his hand and dropped the flowers. Fragrant, obedient, they beheaded themselves on Saina’s salvaged-wood floors.\n\n- Jade Chang, The Wangs vs. the World\n|\nDeception and self-deception are intimately intertwined. We fool ourselves in order to fool others, and we fool others in order to fool ourselves.\n\n- Clancy Martin, The Philosophy of Decepti